LPR+ is a wrapper and extension layer for program-reduction experiments. It
does not redistribute the LPR artifact, Perses, Vulcan, C-Reduce, the LPR
token counter, or the LPR Docker image as part of the Python package.

External tools used by typical LPR+ workflows include:

- LPR: https://github.com/zhangxiaosa/LPR
- Perses: https://github.com/uw-pluverse/perses
- Vulcan: distributed with the LPR artifact
- C-Reduce: https://github.com/csmith-project/creduce
- Docker image m492zhan/lpr:latest: distributed externally

Perses is licensed under GPLv3. The local LPR artifact inspected during this
work did not include an explicit LICENSE file. Users are responsible for
obtaining and using those external tools under their upstream terms.

